# API Validation & Error Handling

Referensi lengkap: `docs/standards/ERROR-HANDLING-VALIDATION.md`

## Response Envelope (Wajib)

```typescript
// Success
return { success: true, data: result, meta?: paginationMeta };

// Error — throw HttpException, filter maps to envelope
throw new ConflictException({
  code: ErrorCodes.INSUFFICIENT_STOCK,
  message: 'Stok produk tidak mencukupi.',
  details: [{ field: 'items[0].quantity', message: 'Stok tersedia: 3' }],
});
```

Import types & codes from `@barokah/shared`:

```typescript
import { ErrorCodes, type ApiSuccessResponse, type ValidationErrorDetail } from '@barokah/shared';
```

## DTO Validation

Every request DTO must use `class-validator` + `class-transformer`:

```typescript
import { IsUUID, IsInt, Min, Max, Matches, ValidateNested, IsOptional } from 'class-validator';
import { Type } from 'class-transformer';

export class PaginationQueryDto {
  @Type(() => Number)
  @IsInt({ message: 'Halaman harus bilangan bulat' })
  @Min(1, { message: 'Halaman minimal 1' })
  page: number = 1;

  @Type(() => Number)
  @IsInt()
  @Min(1)
  @Max(100, { message: 'Limit maksimal 100' })
  limit: number = 20;
}

export class MoneyAmountDto {
  @IsInt({ message: 'Nominal harus integer rupiah' })
  @Min(0, { message: 'Nominal tidak boleh negatif' })
  amount: number;
}
```

### Format Rules

| Field | Rule | Never |
|-------|------|-------|
| Money | `@IsInt()` rupiah or `@Matches(/^\d+(\.\d{1,2})?$/)` Decimal string | `number` float |
| UUID | `@IsUUID('4')` | plain `@IsString()` for IDs |
| Date | `@IsISO8601()` | locale date strings |
| Barcode | `@Matches(/^[0-9A-Za-z\-]{4,32}$/)` | empty allowed for optional only |
| Qty | `@IsInt()` `@Min(1)` | float, zero, negative |

## Validation Layers

```typescript
// Layer 1: DTO (automatic via ValidationPipe) → 422 VALIDATION_FAILED

// Layer 2: Service business rules
async createTransaction(dto: CreateTransactionDto, ctx: TenantContext) {
  const shift = await this.shiftService.getOpenShift(ctx.outletId);
  if (!shift) {
    throw new UnprocessableEntityException({
      code: ErrorCodes.SHIFT_NOT_OPEN,
      message: 'Shift belum dibuka. Buka shift terlebih dahulu.',
    });
  }
  // ...
}
```

## HTTP Status Mapping

| Exception | HTTP | When |
|-----------|------|------|
| `BadRequestException` | 400 | Malformed input |
| `UnauthorizedException` | 401 | Missing/invalid token |
| `ForbiddenException` | 403 | RBAC fail |
| `NotFoundException` | 404 | Resource not found (scoped) |
| `ConflictException` | 409 | Business conflict (stock, duplicate) |
| `UnprocessableEntityException` | 422 | Valid format, invalid state |
| `InternalServerErrorException` | 500 | Unexpected — log full error, return generic message |

Always include `code` from `ErrorCodes` enum in exception payload.

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Return error manually from controller
return { success: false, error: 'something went wrong' };

// ❌ Expose stack trace
catch (e) { throw new InternalServerErrorException(e.stack); }

// ❌ Hardcoded error strings
throw new ConflictException('insufficient stock');

// ❌ Float money
const total = price * 1.11;

// ❌ Skip tenant scope then return 404 for wrong tenant data
```

## ValidationPipe (main.ts)

Already configured — do not weaken:

```typescript
new ValidationPipe({
  whitelist: true,
  forbidNonWhitelisted: true,
  transform: true,
});
```

Enhance with custom `exceptionFactory` to map class-validator errors → `ValidationErrorDetail[]` with `ErrorCodes.VALIDATION_FAILED`.

